This paper is about natural language generation, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning models for generating natural language, which suggests that it could also be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of semantic attributes and syntactic dependency information, which are related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and neural networks (cs.NE), respectively.
